This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it presents a method for automatically recognizing medication mentions in tweets using natural language processing techniques. It also involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a common approach in the field of computational linguistics. 

It could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as the paper involves the task of identifying relevant information (medication mentions) from a large corpus of tweets. 

The paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves the analysis of data from Twitter, a popular social network. 

The use of ensemble learning and deep neural networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category as it involves the analysis of user-generated content on a social network, which could have implications for privacy and security.
